video.title: The Great Food Truck Race
video.synopsis: Food truck teams compete as they cruise across the country, trying to outsell one another in each city to avoid elimination and land a big cash prize.

episodes.synopsis: Seven top food trucks race cross-country for a $50,000 grand prize. The contest begins with a twist when the starting line moves 100 miles south.
episodes.title: Let's Get Rolling!

episodes.synopsis: On the outskirts of Santa Fe, the remaining six competitors get a new element of their challenge: They must create a new dish using local chilies.
episodes.title: Chile Santa Fe

episodes.synopsis: In Fort Worth, contestants must butcher a side of beef and employ it in a unique dish, unaware of the event's secret judge or the huge payout.
episodes.title: Truckin' to Texas

episodes.synopsis: Bad weather greets the final four in New Orleans, where they're told to close shop. Only creating the perfect catfish dish will allow them to reopen.
episodes.title: Big Trouble in the Big Easy

episodes.synopsis: The contestants face two unique challenges: bringing the appeal of food trucks to a small Tennessee town and making a five-course meal for cowboys.
episodes.title: Small Town Trouble

episodes.synopsis: The last two contestants head for New York City, where they compete to make a sales goal in each of the five boroughs. And, as usual, there's a twist.
episodes.title: New York Plate of Mind

episodes.synopsis: This season's race starts in Malibu, California, with a challenge incorporating one lobster and local ingredients before the teams head for Las Vegas.
episodes.title: What Happens in Vegas

episodes.synopsis: On the way into Salt Lake City, the teams are challenged to create custom sausage. Tyler then shakes things up by asking the busy trucks to relocate.
episodes.title: A Pinch of Salt Lake City

episodes.synopsis: Tyler and Robin Roberts of "Good Morning America" announce a challenge whose winner will appear on local Denver TV, landing a big advantage.
episodes.title: Rocky Mountain Highs and Lows

episodes.synopsis: At Kansas State University, the teams are challenged to create an exclusive signature dish for graduation weekend ... on a student budget.
episodes.title: Big Bites, Little Apple

episodes.synopsis: In Memphis,Tennessee, the world's barbecue capital, the final four teams have four hours to turn a 100-pound hog into a mouthwatering masterpiece.
episodes.title: Hog Wild in Memphis

episodes.synopsis: In Atlanta, Tyler challenges the teams to prepare a dish with Georgia trademarks peaches and peanuts, which they must wheedle from the locals.
episodes.title: Midnight Truck to Georgia

episodes.synopsis: The final two race to earn $15,000 and get to the finish line in South Beach, Florida. The grand prize is at stake, but naturally, there's a twist.
episodes.title: Miami Heat

episodes.synopsis: Eight teams of aspiring food truck owners arrive in Long Beach, California, and kick off their journey in the birthplace of food trucks: Los Angeles.
episodes.title: 3,559 Miles to a Dream

episodes.synopsis: The seven remaining teams roll into Flagstaff, Arizona, where a Truck Stop challenge requires them to create a dish featuring prickly pear cactus.
episodes.title: Attitude at High Altitude

episodes.synopsis: The teams visit a minor-league baseball stadium in Amarillo, Texas. Tyler challenges them to add a ballpark-inspired special to their menus.
episodes.title: Food Trucks Are Bigger in TX

episodes.synopsis: The teams head to the bustling college town of Fayetteville, Arkansas, where they must create an amazing breakfast dish using Kellogg's Pop Tarts.
episodes.title: Baby Got Razorback

episodes.synopsis: In Nashville, the Truck Stop Challenge requires teams to create a down-home country-style picnic for country music stars Joey + Rory.
episodes.title: Music City Madness

episodes.synopsis: The final three teams roll into Cleveland, where they're challenged to create a delectable appetizer featuring a ripe Ohio tomato.
episodes.title: Mistake by the Lake?

episodes.synopsis: The final two teams race to Boston to begin selling. In the middle of their shift, Tyler tells them they must add a lobster dish to the menu.
episodes.title: Where in the World Is Lubec?

episodes.synopsis: In Los Angeles, Tyler Florence meets the teams fighting to win the grand prize. The first challenge requires them to sell a $20 signature dish.
episodes.title: I Left My Food Cart in San Francisco

episodes.synopsis: The seven remaining teams head to Portland, where Tyler challenges them to go the entire first day without restocking their supplies.
episodes.title: A Strange Brew in Portland

episodes.synopsis: In Pocatello, Idaho, the teams purge all meat and potatoes from their menus, then dig up potatoes for new menus.
episodes.title: Potatoes in Pocatello

episodes.synopsis: The remaining teams meet Tyler at Mount Rushmore, then go shopping in Rapid City, South Dakota, and butcher a side of bison at a ranch.
episodes.title: About Face in South Dakota

episodes.synopsis: In Minneapolis, all items must be served on a stick. A second challenge in St. Paul has the teams selling dishes made with Spam.
episodes.title: Twin Cities Double Trouble

episodes.synopsis: The teams face a pizza challenge judged by Chicago mayor Rahm Emanuel, followed by an energetic Speed Bump and a hot dog challenge.
episodes.title: Chicago: A Food Truck Town

episodes.synopsis: In the Great Food Truck Race finale, the teams cover the East Coast, ending their journey at the Lincoln Memorial in Washington, D.C.
episodes.title: Food Truck Capital Gains

episodes.synopsis: Tyler Florence welcomes eight new teams to Santa Barbara, California, where they must define their brands and create a signature dish.
episodes.title: Venice Beach Brawl

episodes.synopsis: Tyler meets the teams in Tucson, Arizona, where they must come up with a creative marketing campaign and put their twists on a local hot dog favorite.
episodes.title: Hot Doggin' It in Tucson

episodes.synopsis: In Austin, Texas, the teams pair up to sell together all weekend long. Then they're sent to a Match.com event to feed hungry singles.
episodes.title: Dinner Dates, Austin Style

episodes.synopsis: In Oklahoma City, Tyler tests the teams' time-management skills, penalizing the team who takes the longest to get their day started.
episodes.title: High Steaks in OKC

episodes.synopsis: When the final four teams hit the streets of St. Louis, Tyler gives them a challenge illustrating how a premium product is as good as money in bank.
episodes.title: Beat Me in St. Louis

episodes.synopsis: The three remaining teams roll into Mobile, Alabama, where Tyler challenges them to cook locally. One team scores nearly 100 pounds of free shrimp.
episodes.title: Shrimpin' Ain't Easy

episodes.synopsis: In the grand finale, teams must revisit each of the six lessons learned throughout the race on an epic road trip from Tampa to Key West, Florida.
episodes.title: Winning Keys in Key West
